'''Consular Lookout and Support System''' ('''CLASS''') is an automated system managed by the Bureau of Consular Affairs under the [[United States Department of State]] used for name checks of visa and passport applicants in support of issuance processing and document verification.<ref name=pia>{{cite web|url = https://2001-2009.state.gov/documents/organization/96128.pdf|title = U.S. Department of State Privacy Impact Assessment Summary: Consular Lookout and Support System (CLASS)|date = May 22, 2007|accessdate = November 21, 2017|publisher = [[United States Department of State]]}}</ref> It is described in [[Foreign Affairs Manual|9 FAM 303.3-2(B)]].<ref>{{cite web|url = https://fam.state.gov/fam/09FAM/09FAM030303.html|title = 9 FAM 303.3 (U) CLASS - CONSULAR LOOKOUT AND SUPPORT SYSTEM|date = August 11, 2017|accessdate = November 21, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url = http://international.cua.edu/ImmigrationBasics/arrests.cfm|title = The Effect of Unlawful Behavior on Immigration Status|publisher = The Catholic University of America|accessdate = November 21, 2017}}</ref>

== Sources and users of data ==

Data from CLASS is primarily used for visa and passport processing by the Bureau of Consular Affairs, and in particular finding people who may be ineligible for a passport or visa.<ref name=pia/> CLASS only contains ''lookout'' data, i.e., data on people who pose a potential security threat to the United States, based on the data sources below.

CLASS data may also be shared with, and be modified based on information from, the following other agencies of the United States government:<ref name=pia/>

* [[United States Department of State]]
* [[U.S. Department of Homeland Security]] ([[U.S. Customs and Border Protection]], [[U.S. Immigration and Customs Enforcement]], [[Terrorist Screening Center]])
* [[United States Department of Justice]] ([[Interpol]], [[Federal Bureau of Investigation]], [[Drug Enforcement Administration]], and [[United States Marshals Service]])
* [[U.S. Health and Human Services]

CLASS supplements the [[Consular Consolidated Database]] (CCD), the main database used to inform consular decisions.

